creator: Jesse Pope
description:
LibriVox volunteers bring you 10 recordings of A Valentine (from an Old Lover) by Jessie Pope. This was the Weekly Poetry project for Feb. 2, 2014. Read in English by Claudia Salto; drakaunus; fshort; Holly McGuire; Jason Mills; Julia Niedermaier; expatiate; Lee Ann Howlett; Leonard Wilson and ravenotation. Jessie Pope was an extremely patriotic English poet, writer and journalist, who remains best known for her patriotic motivational poems published during World War I. This poem is from Paper Pellets (1907), an anthology of humorous verse. (Summary from Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (11MB)
